<h1>{{ title }}</h1>

<p>
	This page demonstrates the paired shortcodes available for creating layouts
	and content boxes with action buttons.
</p>

<h2>Hero Section</h2>

<p>
	The <code>hero</code> shortcode creates a full-width hero section with
	optional background image, title, subtitle, and action buttons.
</p>

{%
	hero
	title="Welcome to Our Platform",
	subtitle="Build beautiful websites with ease using our modern theme framework",
	align="center",
	height="350px"
%}
	{% heroButton url="/about", variant="primary" %}Get Started{% endheroButton %}
	{% heroButton url="/blog", variant="secondary" %}Learn More{% endheroButton %}
{% endhero %}

<h3>Hero Usage</h3>

<pre><code class="language-nunjucks">{% raw %}{%
	hero
	title="Welcome to Our Platform",
	subtitle="Build beautiful websites with ease",
	align="center",
	height="350px"
%}
	{% heroButton url="/about", variant="primary" %}Get Started{% endheroButton %}
	{% heroButton url="/blog", variant="secondary" %}Learn More{% endheroButton %}
{% endhero %}{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h3>Hero Parameters</h3>

<ul>
	<li><code>title</code> - Main heading text</li>
	<li><code>subtitle</code> - Secondary text below the title</li>
	<li><code>background</code> - URL to background image</li>
	<li><code>backgroundColor</code> - Fallback background color</li>
	<li>
		<code>align</code> - Text alignment: "left", "center", or "right" (default:
		"center")
	</li>
	<li><code>height</code> - Minimum height (default: "auto")</li>
	<li>
		<code>overlay</code> - Show dark overlay on background image (default: true)
	</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h2>Content Grid with Boxes</h2>

<p>
	The <code>contentGrid</code> shortcode creates a responsive grid layout, while
	<code>box</code> creates individual content boxes with optional action links.
</p>

{% contentGrid cols=3, gap="1.5rem" %}
	{% box title="Fast Performance", link="/about", linkText="Learn More" %}
		<p>
			Built with modern tools and optimized for speed. Your site loads
			instantly.
		</p>
	{% endbox %}
	{% box title="Easy Customization", link="/about", linkText="Explore" %}
		<p>
			Override any theme component with the cascade system. Your code always
			wins.
		</p>
	{% endbox %}
	{% box title="Feature Bundles", link="/blog", linkText="See Examples" %}
		<p>
			Load JavaScript features only on pages that need them with opt-in bundles.
		</p>
	{% endbox %}
{% endcontentGrid %}

<h3>Grid Usage</h3>

<pre><code class="language-nunjucks">{% raw %}{% contentGrid cols=3, gap="1.5rem" %}
	{% box title="Fast Performance", link="/about", linkText="Learn More" %}
		<p>Built with modern tools and optimized for speed.</p>
	{% endbox %}
	{% box title="Easy Customization", link="/about", linkText="Explore" %}
		<p>Override any theme component with the cascade system.</p>
	{% endbox %}
	{% box title="Feature Bundles", link="/blog", linkText="See Examples" %}
		<p>Load JavaScript features only on pages that need them.</p>
	{% endbox %}
{% endcontentGrid %}{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h3>Grid Parameters</h3>

<ul>
	<li>
		<code>cols</code> - Number of columns (default: 3). Responsive: 3 cols
		&rarr; 2 cols (768px) &rarr; 1 col (480px)
	</li>
	<li><code>gap</code> - Gap between items (default: "1rem")</li>
	<li><code>className</code> - Additional CSS class for the grid container</li>
</ul>

<h3>Box Parameters</h3>

<ul>
	<li><code>title</code> - Box heading</li>
	<li><code>link</code> - URL for the call-to-action link</li>
	<li><code>linkText</code> - Text for the link (default: "Learn More")</li>
	<li><code>className</code> - Additional CSS class for the box</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h2>Two-Column Grid Example</h2>

{% contentGrid cols=2, gap="2rem" %}
	{% box title="Development" %}
		<p>
			Run <code>npm run dev</code> to start the development server with hot
			reload.
		</p>
		<p>Changes to content, templates, and styles trigger instant updates.</p>
	{% endbox %}
	{% box title="Production Build" %}
		<p>Run <code>npm run build</code> for optimized production output.</p>
		<p>Includes CSS purging, critical CSS extraction, and HTML minification.</p>
	{% endbox %}
{% endcontentGrid %}

<hr />

